1
00:00:01,102 --> 00:00:03,187
<i>Stocks and bonds are moving higher...</i>

2
00:00:03,438 --> 00:00:05,857
Why are we watching
the Business Channel?

3
00:00:06,107 --> 00:00:10,945
Because the other day I saw there was
a stock with my initials, MEG, on it.

4
00:00:11,195 --> 00:00:13,906
Sometimes it takes two or three hours
before it comes up again.

5
00:00:14,157 --> 00:00:17,285
But when it does, it's exciting.

6
00:00:17,535 --> 00:00:21,039
Okay, honey, you really need a job.

7
00:00:21,289 --> 00:00:24,042
Dad says he knows someone
you can call for an interview.

8
00:00:24,292 --> 00:00:28,796
Right there! That's the third
sign today. Right there.

9
00:00:29,047 --> 00:00:32,842
On behalf of everyone,
I'd just like to say, "Huh?"

10
00:00:33,092 --> 00:00:36,471
No, you just said "dad."
And everywhere I go today...

11
00:00:36,721 --> 00:00:39,182
...I keep getting signs
telling me to go see my father.

12
00:00:39,432 --> 00:00:44,270
Like when I was walking over here
and I passed a buffet.

13
00:00:44,687 --> 00:00:47,982
Which is my father's last name.

14
00:00:48,232 --> 00:00:50,068
And they were serving franks...

15
00:00:50,318 --> 00:00:54,322
...which is his first name
minus the "s" at the end.

16
00:00:54,572 --> 00:00:58,409
And there was a rotisserie
with a spinning chicken.

17
00:00:58,660 --> 00:01:01,246
His Indian name?

18
00:01:01,496 --> 00:01:06,334
No. Because I chickened out
the last time...

19
00:01:06,584 --> 00:01:10,129
...when I tried to meet him.
So coincidences? I don't think so.

20
00:01:10,380 --> 00:01:12,548
- Very freaky.
- Eerie.

21
00:01:12,799 --> 00:01:14,550
Who wants the last hamburger?

22
00:01:14,801 --> 00:01:17,136
That's it.
Now I have to go see him.

23
00:01:17,387 --> 00:01:18,179
Why?

24
00:01:18,429 --> 00:01:21,474
Hamburger? McDonald's?

25
00:01:21,724 --> 00:01:26,229
Old McDonald had a farm.
My dad is a pharmacist.

26
00:01:27,527 --> 00:01:32,747
And "E-I-E-I-O" is what your mom
said when your dad left her.

27
00:01:32,936 --> 00:01:33,624
Yes!

28
00:01:34,330 --> 00:01:35,664
- Really?
- No.

29
00:01:37,380 --> 00:01:40,424
The One With the Bullies

30
00:02:23,952 --> 00:02:26,955
Man, I am so beat.

31
00:02:27,206 --> 00:02:29,333
You wanna forget racquetball
and hang out?

32
00:02:29,583 --> 00:02:32,503
Yeah, all right.

33
00:02:34,213 --> 00:02:37,508
- Hey, you're in our seats.
- Sorry, we didn't know.

34
00:02:37,758 --> 00:02:39,635
We were sitting there.

35
00:02:39,885 --> 00:02:42,679
Okay.
There is one more way to say it.

36
00:02:42,930 --> 00:02:46,058
Who knows it?

37
00:02:46,141 --> 00:02:50,646
- Was that supposed to be funny?
- Actually, I was going for colorful.

38
00:02:50,896 --> 00:02:53,148
- What's with this guy?
- What's with you?

39
00:02:53,398 --> 00:02:55,442
Nothing. Nothing's with him.

40
00:02:55,692 --> 00:02:58,695
Enjoy your coffee.

41
00:03:04,117 --> 00:03:06,912
What just happened?

42
00:03:07,162 --> 00:03:10,541
I just took your hat.
See, I can be funny too.

43
00:03:10,791 --> 00:03:13,669
My joke is that I took your hat.

44
00:03:13,919 --> 00:03:16,922
That is funny.

45
00:03:17,172 --> 00:03:19,842
Can I have it back?

46
00:03:26,807 --> 00:03:29,560
You know what?
I think you're very funny.

47
00:03:29,810 --> 00:03:33,939
Kudos on that hat joke.

48
00:03:34,690 --> 00:03:38,026
But come on, guys,
just give him back the hat.

49
00:03:38,277 --> 00:03:40,154
Why should we?

50
00:03:40,404 --> 00:03:43,282
Because it's a special hat.

51
00:03:43,532 --> 00:03:46,285
He bought it because
he was feeling down one day.

52
00:03:46,535 --> 00:03:47,828
So he got the hat...

53
00:03:48,078 --> 00:03:50,664
...to cheer himself up, you know?

54
00:03:50,914 --> 00:03:55,711
- Chandler...
- Stop talking. Stop talking now.

55
00:03:55,919 --> 00:03:58,297
Let me get this straight.
You're stealing my hat?

56
00:03:58,547 --> 00:03:59,465
You got a problem?

57
00:03:59,715 --> 00:04:04,094
I just want to make sure
we're on the same page.

58
00:04:04,811 --> 00:04:08,770
I'm telling you, Rach. I've gone
dad hunting with Phoebe before.

59
00:04:09,115 --> 00:04:12,656
This is a very scary thing for her.
She gets real vulnerable.

60
00:04:13,591 --> 00:04:17,270
That's why we're there.
To, you know, be supportive and crap.

61
00:04:18,091 --> 00:04:21,060
Okay. Will you just let me
know when to do which.

62
00:04:24,112 --> 00:04:25,947
How'd the interview go?

63
00:04:26,198 --> 00:04:28,367
It bit.

64
00:04:28,617 --> 00:04:30,619
It was a '50s theme restaurant.

65
00:04:30,869 --> 00:04:34,456
I'd have to cook in a costume
and dance on the counter.

66
00:04:34,706 --> 00:04:37,250
I was a sous chef
at "Café des Artistes."

67
00:04:37,501 --> 00:04:41,880
How can I take a job where I have
to make Laverne-and-Curly Fries?

68
00:04:42,130 --> 00:04:43,965
- Don't do it.
- How can I not do it?

69
00:04:44,216 --> 00:04:46,009
I have $ 127 in the bank!

70
00:04:46,259 --> 00:04:49,179
Monica, relax. Go get a beer.

71
00:04:49,429 --> 00:04:50,681
I don't want a beer.

72
00:04:50,931 --> 00:04:53,934
Who said it was for you?

73
00:05:01,066 --> 00:05:02,359
What's the matter?

74
00:05:02,609 --> 00:05:05,779
Some mean guys at the coffeehouse
took my hat.

75
00:05:06,029 --> 00:05:07,698
- No!
- You're kidding?

76
00:05:07,948 --> 00:05:10,325
It was ridiculous.
These guys were bullies.

77
00:05:10,575 --> 00:05:12,536
Actual bullies.

78
00:05:12,786 --> 00:05:18,250
We're grownups. This kind of stuff
isn't supposed to happen anymore.

79
00:05:19,710 --> 00:05:23,880
Oh, no, wait a minute.
I have no one.

80
00:05:26,133 --> 00:05:28,677
Let's go down there
and get your hat back.

81
00:05:28,927 --> 00:05:34,599
Forget it. It's probably stripped
and sold for parts by now.

82
00:05:35,392 --> 00:05:37,185
- I went up!
- What?

83
00:05:37,436 --> 00:05:40,647
My stock, MEG, it went up two points.

84
00:05:40,897 --> 00:05:45,068
Do you realize that if I'd invested
my $ 127 in myself yesterday...

85
00:05:45,319 --> 00:05:50,115
...that I'd, like, have
a lot more than that today.

86
00:05:50,365 --> 00:05:52,784
You know what?
I'm going to do it.

87
00:05:53,035 --> 00:05:55,245
- Do what?
- Put all my money in me.

88
00:05:55,495 --> 00:05:58,248
You don't know a thing
about the stock market.

89
00:05:58,498 --> 00:06:01,626
What's to know?
Buy, sell. High, low. Bears, bulls.

90
00:06:01,877 --> 00:06:03,670
Yes, Manhattan.

91
00:06:03,920 --> 00:06:06,340
Telephone number for the stock...

92
00:06:06,590 --> 00:06:09,926
...selling store.

93
00:06:18,894 --> 00:06:22,105
See? I told you these pillows
would be a good idea.

94
00:06:22,356 --> 00:06:24,107
Oh, God.

95
00:06:24,358 --> 00:06:26,401
Here we go.

96
00:06:26,652 --> 00:06:30,989
For the first time in my life,
I'm gonna say, "Hi, Birth Father!"

97
00:06:31,239 --> 00:06:32,866
- We love you. We're here for you.
- Good luck.

98
00:06:33,116 --> 00:06:35,827
Thanks.

99
00:06:38,205 --> 00:06:40,540
Hey, Rach, you want some sandwich?

100
00:06:40,791 --> 00:06:42,292
What is in that?

101
00:06:42,542 --> 00:06:44,711
Olive loaf and ham spread. No mayo.

102
00:06:44,962 --> 00:06:49,383
No, because mayo,
that would make it gross.

103
00:06:51,969 --> 00:06:54,471
- Run, Phoebe, run!
- No, no, doggy, please!

104
00:06:54,721 --> 00:06:58,350
I do so want to love all animals.
Please, no. Back off!

105
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:00,602
- You got a bone?
- Are you kidding?

106
00:07:00,852 --> 00:07:03,730
Look, kibbles! Bits!

107
00:07:03,981 --> 00:07:08,735
Get the hell off my leg,
you yippity piece of crap!

108
00:07:14,324 --> 00:07:17,077
Okay. All right. We have a problem.

109
00:07:17,327 --> 00:07:20,205
Why don't you take his trampoline?

110
00:07:20,455 --> 00:07:24,001
Okay, here, I know what we can do.

111
00:07:24,835 --> 00:07:28,130
Okay, doggy, get the sandwich!

112
00:07:28,380 --> 00:07:32,217
Go get the sandwich!
Good doggy. Get the sandwich!

113
00:07:32,467 --> 00:07:36,138
The dog will lick himself
but he will not touch your sandwich.

114
00:07:36,388 --> 00:07:38,557
What does that tell you?

115
00:07:38,807 --> 00:07:42,436
- Lf he's not going to eat it, I will.
- Are you crazy?

116
00:07:42,686 --> 00:07:45,939
He's just a little dog.

117
00:07:51,653 --> 00:07:53,363
- Hey.
- What?

118
00:07:53,614 --> 00:07:56,366
Do you have to be a Century 21
real-estate agent...

119
00:07:56,617 --> 00:08:00,495
...to get to wear those cool jackets?

120
00:08:01,079 --> 00:08:05,292
Do you say this stuff to girls?

121
00:08:06,460 --> 00:08:09,546
Isn't that the guy
who used to wear your hat?

122
00:08:09,796 --> 00:08:13,216
And look where they're sitting.

123
00:08:14,635 --> 00:08:18,931
You're joking, right?
You guys just walked through the door.

124
00:08:19,181 --> 00:08:21,391
Maybe we didn't make it clear enough.

125
00:08:21,642 --> 00:08:24,228
This couch belongs to us.

126
00:08:24,478 --> 00:08:27,981
I'll tell you what,
you call the couch...

127
00:08:28,232 --> 00:08:32,069
...and then we'll call the couch...

128
00:08:32,236 --> 00:08:35,155
...and we'll see who it comes to.

129
00:08:38,551 --> 00:08:40,008
You know what I don't
like you about you?

130
00:08:40,708 --> 00:08:43,409
- You always got something to say.
- Well, that...

131
00:08:46,905 --> 00:08:50,576
You know, I keep wondering
why you two are still sitting here.

132
00:08:50,826 --> 00:08:52,828
All right, that's it.

133
00:08:53,078 --> 00:08:55,122
I have had enough of this.

134
00:08:55,372 --> 00:08:57,541
Gunther.

135
00:08:57,791 --> 00:09:01,462
These guys are trying
to take our seat.

136
00:09:01,712 --> 00:09:03,881
Fellas, these guys were here first.

137
00:09:04,131 --> 00:09:06,175
Oh, sorry, didn't realize.

138
00:09:06,425 --> 00:09:07,426
There you go.

139
00:09:07,676 --> 00:09:11,221
Thank you, Gunther.

140
00:09:12,681 --> 00:09:15,684
We didn't want to have
to go and do that.

141
00:09:15,934 --> 00:09:18,270
He told on us?

142
00:09:18,520 --> 00:09:19,730
You told on us?

143
00:09:19,980 --> 00:09:24,443
Well, pal, you didn't
give me much of a choice.

144
00:09:24,693 --> 00:09:28,530
- Don't play with his thing.
- I know.

145
00:09:29,365 --> 00:09:30,991
All right.

146
00:09:31,241 --> 00:09:34,536
Let's take this outside.

147
00:09:35,371 --> 00:09:40,167
"Let's take this outside?"

148
00:09:41,043 --> 00:09:43,295
Who talks like that?

149
00:09:43,545 --> 00:09:47,883
The guy who's about to kick your ass
talks like that.

150
00:09:48,133 --> 00:09:51,261
You had to ask.

151
00:09:53,472 --> 00:09:55,808
Okay, okay, look. See...

152
00:09:56,058 --> 00:10:01,021
...the thing is, we're not gonna
fight you guys.

153
00:10:01,271 --> 00:10:02,439
Here's the deal.

154
00:10:02,690 --> 00:10:09,196
You won't have to, so long as you
never ever show your faces here again.

155
00:10:12,992 --> 00:10:17,329
I think you played
the Gunther card too soon.

156
00:10:22,084 --> 00:10:24,795
Hey, Pheebs, I think you're good to go.

157
00:10:25,045 --> 00:10:27,840
Yeah, I don't know.

158
00:10:28,298 --> 00:10:29,341
What's the matter?

159
00:10:29,591 --> 00:10:32,428
I just think that this was
a really bad sign.

160
00:10:32,678 --> 00:10:36,932
Like the beast at the threshold.

161
00:10:37,182 --> 00:10:41,979
It's just I have no family left,
except for my grandmother.

162
00:10:42,229 --> 00:10:45,232
But let's face it, she's not
gonna be around forever.

163
00:10:45,482 --> 00:10:48,444
Despite what she says.

164
00:10:48,569 --> 00:10:54,616
And I have a sister who I've barely
spoken to since we shared a womb.

165
00:10:54,867 --> 00:10:56,910
I don't know. This is my real father...

166
00:10:57,161 --> 00:11:00,456
...and I want things to be,
like, just right.

167
00:11:00,706 --> 00:11:02,333
I completely understand.

168
00:11:02,583 --> 00:11:05,252
Whatever you need.

169
00:11:05,294 --> 00:11:07,129
Hey, you want to go home?

170
00:11:07,379 --> 00:11:11,091
Okay, thanks. Sorry, again.

171
00:11:28,942 --> 00:11:32,196
What was that?

172
00:11:34,990 --> 00:11:39,370
I'm guessing the threshold's clear now.

173
00:11:42,948 --> 00:11:45,597
I want to buy five shares of SGJ
and I wanna buy them now.

174
00:11:45,734 --> 00:11:48,195
Come on, time is money, my friend!

175
00:11:48,445 --> 00:11:51,073
Thank you!

176
00:11:51,365 --> 00:11:53,241
"Time is money, my friend?"

177
00:11:53,492 --> 00:11:55,619
You missed
"Takes money to make money"...

178
00:11:55,869 --> 00:12:00,207
...and "Don't make me come down there
and kick your Wall Street butt."

179
00:12:00,457 --> 00:12:03,794
I made $ 17 before breakfast.
What have you done?

180
00:12:04,044 --> 00:12:08,882
I had breakfast here,
so technically I saved $3.50.

181
00:12:09,132 --> 00:12:10,550
How did you make $17?

182
00:12:10,801 --> 00:12:13,095
Well, my financially
challenged friends...

183
00:12:13,345 --> 00:12:17,349
...I split my money and I bought
some shares of CHP and ZXY.

184
00:12:17,599 --> 00:12:18,809
How come those?

185
00:12:19,059 --> 00:12:24,439
Well, CHP because I used to have a
crush on Erik Estrada.

186
00:12:24,690 --> 00:12:28,860
And ZXY because I think
it sounds "zexy."

187
00:12:29,111 --> 00:12:31,071
What happened to MEG?

188
00:12:31,321 --> 00:12:33,740
MEG was good for me, but I dumped her.

189
00:12:33,991 --> 00:12:38,245
My motto is, "Get out
before they go down."

190
00:12:38,495 --> 00:12:42,874
That is so not my motto.

191
00:12:48,005 --> 00:12:49,089
How's the dog?

192
00:12:49,339 --> 00:12:52,718
Okay. I talked to the vet.
People are so nice upstate.

193
00:12:52,968 --> 00:12:56,596
He said the little fella's gonna be
okay, and I can get him tomorrow.

194
00:12:56,847 --> 00:12:58,432
- Good.
- Thank God.

195
00:12:58,682 --> 00:13:01,393
But he did have to have
a bunch of stitches.

196
00:13:01,643 --> 00:13:05,981
And he said that only once in a blue
moon does a dog's ear grow back.

197
00:13:06,231 --> 00:13:09,943
So still hoping.

198
00:13:10,819 --> 00:13:15,782
Now are you going to call your dad
to let him know that his dog is okay?

199
00:13:16,033 --> 00:13:19,536
I don't want to meet my father
over the phone.

200
00:13:19,786 --> 00:13:22,331
What will I say,
"Hi, I'm the daughter you abandoned."

201
00:13:22,581 --> 00:13:25,917
"Oh, by the way, I broke your dog."

202
00:13:26,168 --> 00:13:30,255
Hey, Pheebs, if you want, I'll do it.

203
00:13:30,714 --> 00:13:34,718
Listen, just don't say anything
about me, okay?

204
00:13:34,968 --> 00:13:37,554
Don't...

205
00:13:38,096 --> 00:13:40,682
...be too long with the phone.

206
00:13:40,933 --> 00:13:45,687
She'll be a much better friend
once the market closes.

207
00:13:47,105 --> 00:13:48,065
It's a woman.

208
00:13:48,315 --> 00:13:51,151
So talk to her.

209
00:13:53,153 --> 00:13:56,073
Hello, Mrs. Buffay.

210
00:13:56,239 --> 00:13:59,076
I know where your dog is.

211
00:13:59,326 --> 00:14:03,956
I want you to know he'll be returned
to you almost as good as new...

212
00:14:04,206 --> 00:14:05,958
...within 24 hours.

213
00:14:06,208 --> 00:14:09,253
Goodbye.

214
00:14:14,591 --> 00:14:18,178
- Why the voice?
- Hard to say.

215
00:14:20,347 --> 00:14:21,598
Your cappuccino, sir.

216
00:14:21,848 --> 00:14:24,685
Thank you.

217
00:14:26,603 --> 00:14:31,566
- This is better than the coffeehouse.
- Absolutely.

218
00:14:39,032 --> 00:14:41,451
How come it's not mixing
with the water?

219
00:14:41,702 --> 00:14:44,162
The package says to keep it moving.

220
00:14:44,413 --> 00:14:48,333
Stir and drink, never let it settle.

221
00:14:52,337 --> 00:14:54,131
This is ridiculous.

222
00:14:54,381 --> 00:14:57,092
After I get back from
my niece's christening...

223
00:14:57,342 --> 00:15:01,722
...I'll go to the coffeehouse with you
and we'll have a cup of coffee.

224
00:15:01,972 --> 00:15:05,893
No problem. Joey's there.

225
00:15:09,396 --> 00:15:14,443
I don't want to have to have Joey with
me every time I want decent coffee.

226
00:15:14,693 --> 00:15:18,196
And I don't want to drink
cappuccino with a "k."

227
00:15:18,447 --> 00:15:21,491
I say you and I go
and stand up to those guys.

228
00:15:21,742 --> 00:15:25,704
All right, hang on
a second there, Custer.

229
00:15:25,746 --> 00:15:28,165
Ross, have you ever
been beaten up before?

230
00:15:28,415 --> 00:15:29,541
Yeah, sure.

231
00:15:29,791 --> 00:15:33,420
By someone besides Monica?

232
00:15:33,670 --> 00:15:34,504
So what?

233
00:15:34,755 --> 00:15:38,717
So we get beaten up. Maybe that's
something a man has to go through.

234
00:15:38,967 --> 00:15:41,970
Like a rite of passage or something.

235
00:15:42,221 --> 00:15:46,141
Couldn't we just lose
our virginities again?

236
00:15:46,391 --> 00:15:48,501
Because I think actually
mine's growing back.

237
00:15:50,149 --> 00:15:52,083
All right. Are you with me
or not? Come on.

238
00:15:52,685 --> 00:15:55,264
All right. I'm with you. Just...

239
00:15:56,193 --> 00:15:58,866
...let me put on a clean pair
of underwear for the hospital.

240
00:16:01,722 --> 00:16:03,849
- I need $100.
- What?

241
00:16:04,099 --> 00:16:06,059
Welcome home.

242
00:16:06,309 --> 00:16:07,728
- I need $100.
- For what?

243
00:16:07,978 --> 00:16:10,439
- To get back in the game.
- When did you get out?

244
00:16:10,689 --> 00:16:13,525
I lost it all. I lost it.

245
00:16:13,775 --> 00:16:18,572
I've come to terms with it,
you have to, too.

246
00:16:19,990 --> 00:16:23,326
Look, Mon, I'm really sorry.

247
00:16:23,577 --> 00:16:25,203
Where are we on the $ 100?

248
00:16:25,454 --> 00:16:26,663
I don't have it.

249
00:16:26,913 --> 00:16:29,082
But I need it!

250
00:16:29,332 --> 00:16:31,710
Otherwise, I'll have to
take that diner job.

251
00:16:31,960 --> 00:16:37,716
You know, with the dancing
and the costumes.

252
00:16:39,342 --> 00:16:43,346
I don't want to have to wear
flame-retardant boobs.

253
00:16:43,597 --> 00:16:47,684
Nobody does, honey.

254
00:16:50,103 --> 00:16:51,354
Noodle!

255
00:16:51,605 --> 00:16:55,984
Oh, my God. What the hell
happened to my dog?

256
00:16:56,234 --> 00:16:57,319
It was an accident.

257
00:16:57,569 --> 00:17:00,864
And the woman who did this
would never hurt a dog on purpose.

258
00:17:01,114 --> 00:17:03,825
She's a vegetarian.

259
00:17:04,076 --> 00:17:05,243
Are these stitches?

260
00:17:05,494 --> 00:17:09,748
Yeah, eight of them.
That's 56 to him.

261
00:17:09,998 --> 00:17:12,751
If it's raining, you can't
let him look up...

262
00:17:13,001 --> 00:17:16,671
...because that cone
will fill up fast.

263
00:17:17,047 --> 00:17:18,715
Thanks for bringing back
what's left of him.

264
00:17:18,965 --> 00:17:22,052
- Is Frank home?
- How do you know Frank?

265
00:17:22,302 --> 00:17:26,890
Just from a long time ago.
Is he here?

266
00:17:31,144 --> 00:17:33,689
What?

267
00:17:34,272 --> 00:17:35,649
I mean Frank Senior.

268
00:17:35,899 --> 00:17:37,609
He went out for groceries.

269
00:17:37,859 --> 00:17:39,361
Will he be back soon?

270
00:17:39,611 --> 00:17:44,533
He left four years ago.
We're expecting him back any minute.

271
00:17:45,325 --> 00:17:46,368
I'm gonna go.

272
00:17:46,618 --> 00:17:48,954
I'm sorry about the dog.
Everything.

273
00:17:49,204 --> 00:17:50,747
I'm sorry.

274
00:17:50,998 --> 00:17:52,249
Hey, lady!

275
00:17:52,499 --> 00:17:55,669
Hey, wait up!

276
00:17:58,839 --> 00:18:02,384
- How do you know my dad?
- Well, I don't really.

277
00:18:02,634 --> 00:18:05,721
Just genetically.

278
00:18:05,971 --> 00:18:08,432
He's kind of my dad too.

279
00:18:08,682 --> 00:18:11,268
Heavy.

280
00:18:12,185 --> 00:18:15,856
So did he ever talk about me... Phoebe?

281
00:18:16,106 --> 00:18:20,235
No, but he didn't really talk
about anything.

282
00:18:20,902 --> 00:18:23,196
Except stilts.

283
00:18:23,447 --> 00:18:25,949
- Stilts?
- Yeah, he loved stilts.

284
00:18:26,199 --> 00:18:30,495
One time, I was upstairs stealing
cigarettes out of my mom's purse...

285
00:18:30,746 --> 00:18:33,123
...and all of a sudden I look over...

286
00:18:33,373 --> 00:18:37,753
...and there's Dad's head,
bobbing past the window.

287
00:18:38,045 --> 00:18:41,048
He just had this big smile on his face
and he was waving...

288
00:18:41,298 --> 00:18:45,636
...because he was happiest
when he was on his stilts.

289
00:18:48,764 --> 00:18:50,807
I don't know what to do with that.

290
00:18:51,058 --> 00:18:53,977
Me neither.

291
00:18:55,812 --> 00:18:59,024
So are you, like, my big sister?

292
00:18:59,274 --> 00:19:02,944
This is huge. You can buy me beer!

293
00:19:03,195 --> 00:19:05,280
I'm not gonna.

294
00:19:05,530 --> 00:19:09,242
But you know what's cool? If you had
a friend named Pete, I could say...

295
00:19:09,493 --> 00:19:12,537
..."I know Pete.
He's friends with my brother."

296
00:19:12,788 --> 00:19:15,666
- I got a friend named Mark.
- That'll work too.

297
00:19:15,916 --> 00:19:17,584
Cool. All right.

298
00:19:17,834 --> 00:19:22,589
So maybe, you know,
I could give you a call sometime.

299
00:19:22,839 --> 00:19:24,424
We could talk or something.

300
00:19:24,675 --> 00:19:26,969
- Yeah, that'd be okay.
- All right.

301
00:19:27,219 --> 00:19:30,347
I'm in the book.

302
00:19:33,475 --> 00:19:35,894
So stilts, huh?

303
00:19:36,144 --> 00:19:42,109
If you want, I can show you where
he hit his head on the rain gutter.

304
00:19:45,320 --> 00:19:50,784
We did it. We're here.
We are standing our ground.

305
00:19:50,867 --> 00:19:55,789
- How long does coffee take?
- Would you come on? Come on!

306
00:19:56,290 --> 00:19:58,959
Thank you.

307
00:20:08,885 --> 00:20:12,848
- There we go.
- I think we proved our point.

308
00:20:13,557 --> 00:20:17,769
- You burn your mouth?
- Cannot feel my tongue.

309
00:20:20,897 --> 00:20:22,774
Bullies! Big bullies!

310
00:20:23,025 --> 00:20:27,696
Look who's here.
It's the weenies.

311
00:20:27,863 --> 00:20:30,574
Did we not make ourselves clear
the other day?

312
00:20:30,824 --> 00:20:32,200
That's why we're here.

313
00:20:32,451 --> 00:20:34,995
Yes, we're standing our ground.

314
00:20:35,245 --> 00:20:37,205
Apparently.

315
00:20:37,456 --> 00:20:38,999
Let's do this already.

316
00:20:39,249 --> 00:20:41,209
You got a weapon?

317
00:20:41,460 --> 00:20:44,212
A nice watch.
I don't want to break it on your ribs.

318
00:20:44,463 --> 00:20:47,257
All right, let's do this.

319
00:20:47,507 --> 00:20:52,095
Question: If I don't care about
my watch, can I use it as a weapon?

320
00:20:52,346 --> 00:20:54,514
- What do you mean?
- It's sharp, it's metal.

321
00:20:54,765 --> 00:20:58,101
I think I can do some
serious damage with it.

322
00:20:58,352 --> 00:21:01,730
No, you can't use your watch.

323
00:21:01,772 --> 00:21:04,024
Or your keys.

324
00:21:04,274 --> 00:21:05,692
Here's what we'll do.

325
00:21:05,943 --> 00:21:09,571
We'll put all keys and watches
in the hat over there.

326
00:21:09,821 --> 00:21:12,407
All right?

327
00:21:12,866 --> 00:21:15,410
All right, come on, man. Let's do it!

328
00:21:15,661 --> 00:21:19,164
Before I forget, are we hitting faces?

329
00:21:19,414 --> 00:21:21,208
Of course. Why wouldn't you hit faces?

330
00:21:21,458 --> 00:21:25,754
I have to work on Monday.
I have a big presentation.

331
00:21:26,004 --> 00:21:28,966
Actually, I gotta show
this apartment tomorrow...

332
00:21:29,216 --> 00:21:33,512
...and this no-faces thing
might not be a bad idea.

333
00:21:33,762 --> 00:21:36,640
Nothing from the neck up.

334
00:21:37,057 --> 00:21:39,393
Or the waist down.

335
00:21:39,643 --> 00:21:43,564
- Dana's ovulating.
- Really? You guys trying again?

336
00:21:43,814 --> 00:21:46,859
Let me get this straight.
We're talking about the middle?

337
00:21:47,109 --> 00:21:48,151
Come on!

338
00:21:48,402 --> 00:21:53,615
You want a piece of this?
I'm standing here!

339
00:21:53,907 --> 00:21:57,452
Those guys are taking our stuff!

340
00:22:00,831 --> 00:22:03,166
God, that was amazing.
That was incredible.

341
00:22:03,417 --> 00:22:06,211
- You guys kicked butt!
- Us? What about you guys?

342
00:22:06,461 --> 00:22:09,298
You really gave it to
old Mr. Clean back there.

343
00:22:09,548 --> 00:22:12,259
- He was a big guy.
- Yeah, he was, wasn't he?

344
00:22:12,509 --> 00:22:14,511
I wouldn't know,
having missed everything.

345
00:22:14,761 --> 00:22:16,805
Don't do that to yourself.

346
00:22:17,055 --> 00:22:22,394
Any one of us could have tripped
over that little girl's jump rope.

347
00:22:23,103 --> 00:22:26,940
So listen, guys...

348
00:22:27,191 --> 00:22:29,985
...are we okay here?

349
00:22:30,777 --> 00:22:32,154
We're okay.

350
00:22:32,404 --> 00:22:35,699
So can I have my hat back?

351
00:22:50,798 --> 00:22:53,426
Oh, my God. Look at her.

352
00:22:53,676 --> 00:22:55,845
Hi, Monica!

353
00:22:56,095 --> 00:22:57,263
How's it going?

354
00:22:57,514 --> 00:23:00,099
Hey, nice boobs.

355
00:23:00,350 --> 00:23:03,728
Guys, guys. Check this out.

356
00:23:21,246 --> 00:23:24,374
Excellent.
